        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a user requests to add, modify, update, enhance, change, edit, improve, remove, or delete any part of a flow: 1. Extract the EXACT text of what the user said in their last message in the conversation. 2. Call the EvolveFlow action. The userPrompt parameter is automatically populated with the user&apos;s message from the conversation. DO NOT ask the user for more details. Use whatever they said in their message. DO NOT modify or paraphrase the user&apos;s message. Pass the message exactly as they said it. The EvolveFlow action handles all flow modifications including: (1) Adding new elements (email alerts, record lookups, assignments, decision points, screens, loops, etc.) (2) Modifying existing element properties (email subjects, filter criteria, field values, connections, labels, descriptions, etc.) (3) Removing or deleting elements while maintaining proper flow connections. Examples of user messages that should trigger this:  - &quot;Add an email notification&quot; - &quot;Change the email subject&quot; - &quot;Add a filter&quot; - &quot;Remove the assignment element&quot;</description>
            <developerName>ModifyFlowInstruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>ModifyFlowInstruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
